               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430821-name-1269" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1269" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1269" type="surname" value="WELLER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1269" type="given" value="SAMUEL"></interp>SAMUEL WELLER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a broker, and live in Russell-court, Drury-lane; I have one partner. About half-past ten o'clock on Saturday night, the 5th of August, I was in my parlour—I saw the two prisoners come into the shop—Smith came in first; Barrett stood behind him at the door—Barrett took something off the counter, which was just at the door—I could not see what it was—I came out, and he ran off—I called, "Stop him"—I told my lad to keep Smith while I went after Barrett, but he was gone—when I came back I missed these double-bladed pen-knives, which had been in front of the counter—I asked Smith if he knew the other person—he said he knew nothing at all about him—I gave Smith into custody—the knives have not been found.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430821-name-1270" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1270" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1270" type="surname" value="MILLER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1270" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM MILLER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am in the prosecutor's employ. At about a quarter-past ten o'clock on the night of the 5th of August, I saw the two prisoners at the tobacconist's at the corner of Russell-court—they were in conversation together—that was three or four minutes before they came to our shop—when</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184308210179"></xptr>
               <p>I came back Smith was in custody—I am quite sure he is the one whom I had wen with Barrett before.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430821-name-1271" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1271" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1271" type="surname" value="BAFFIN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1271" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM BAFFIN</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable F</hi> 141.) I was called to the pro<lb></lb>secutor's shop, and received charge of Smith—he said he came to look at a coat, and ask the price, and during that time the other committed the robbery.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430821-name-1272" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1272" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1272" type="surname" value="WEST"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1272" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM WEST</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police constable F</hi> 106.) On the morning of the 7th of August, I went to Lincoln's-court, Drury-lane, and found Barrett in bed—I knocked—his mother opened the door, and asked what I wanted—I said her son—she said, "What has he done?"—Barrett jumped up in bed and said, "It is nothing, only for being with <hi rend="italic">Tom</hi> Monton on Saturday night."</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Smith's Defence.</hi> We were together in Clare-market; I left him at half-past nine o'clock; I went to Russell-court; I was taken into custody because he said a boy behind me had done something.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Barrett's Defence.</hi> I never was with him there; I did not know where he went to.</p>
